  <data name="lblPreConditionHelp.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>&lt;table cellpadding="1px" cellspacing="0px" border="1px"&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Precondition
     &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td&gt;
      Explanation
     &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;td&gt;
     Notes
     &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       '$(Firstname)' = 'sam' 
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Email will be sent only if field firstName is sam. 
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Single quotes around field tokens that can have string values
      &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;/tr&gt;
     
     &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       in('$(Lastname)','sam','sammy')
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Activate workflow only if lastname is sam or sammy. 
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Again note single quotes
      &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;/tr&gt;
     
     &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       (qs:PropertyID) != 1 or '(qs:PropertyName)' = 'Flat'
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Activate only if query string PropertyID is not 1 or PropertyName is equal to Flat.
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Query strings can be used for precondition also notice the use of single quotes
      &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;/tr&gt;
     
     &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       ($(price)+100) &gt; (qs:SecretPrice) 
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Self explanatory.
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       For advanced users
      &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;/tr&gt;
     &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       $(price) &gt; 100 and '$(name)' = 'sam' 
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       Self explanatory.
      &lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;
       For advanced users
      &lt;/td&gt;
     &lt;/tr&gt;
   &lt;/table&gt;</value>
